      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Does look a race between the top three. POINT NEPEAN (1) is a local galloper who has had five starts over jumps - all in hurdles and all with Ryan aboard - for two wins and three minors. First try over the bigger fences and has the big weight but small field suits and will take catching. GOLDEN GARDEN (3) placed in a chase fresh then had a lead-up run when safely held on the flat latest. Returns home and back over fences and expected to go close. FIELD OF LIGHTS (2) will be the big improver. Led throughout for an easy chase win fresh then choked down and was pulled out of the race last time. Has a tongue tie added for this and worth another chance. SANIKA (7) is a local who is a maiden over the jumps but can run well at home.",
